        <condition/>
        <description>16. **Restrict Value Change in List View**  &#13;
From the list view, prevent users from changing the value of a field from **"false"** to **"true."**</description>
        <field>u_active</field>
        <global>true</global>
        <isolate_script>true</isolate_script>
        <messages/>
        <name>Restrict Value Change in List View</name>
        <order/>
        <script><![CDATA[function onCellEdit(sysIDs, table, fieldName, oldValue, newValue) {
    // Field name to restrict changes
    var restrictedField = 'u_active';

    // Check if the edited field is the restricted field
    if (fieldName === restrictedField) {
        // Prevent changing the value from false to true
        if (oldValue === false && newValue === true) {
            // Display an error message
            alert('Changing this field from "false" to "true" is not allowed.');
            return false; // Revert the change
        }
    }

    return true; // Allow other changes
}
]]></script>
